<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-1B6B5918-BE50-4455-8B0C-BF62C907AF58" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-1B6B5918-BE50-4455-8B0C-BF62C907AF58" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to request a license via e-mail</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p ">The licenses of the printer are stored on a Wibu dongle. This USB key is situated in the Windows controller (also called printer license key). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> It is similar as the SAM key that is used to access the SDS and HTML TSM. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure describes how to request a license from your local back-office. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-923181F2-778D-4C5F-BE15-CAD033394C6D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Additional useful information</title><p class="- topic/p ">You only need to retrieve a Dongle summary file (&lt;dongle ID&gt;-SummaryFile.zip) from the printer to create a request. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can get this file via the Settings Editor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This zip file includes all the information required to create a license file: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A &lt;dongle ID&gt;.WibuCmRac file (WiBu dongle context file) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A &lt;dongle ID&gt;.xml file (including the printer hardware identifier value and the printer serial number) 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-8E2C2C62-EA17-419B-9B2F-0FA4DA71CA76" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Prerequisites</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_8D4654E109714EE49EBD0F809E60DB5E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> E-mail address of the person in charge of creating licenses in your local back-office (organization). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The installation wizard must have completed (except license installation) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> System Administrator password is required. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A valid license number for this printer is needed 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A WiBu dongle must be installed on the <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check this if anything goes wrong. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-E061F99E-550A-4BDD-829E-A3B070741606" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> If the controller is replaced by a new one, you need a new WiBu dongle and as a result do a new license request. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is because the license file is partly based on the ‘Hardware identifier’ which is specific for each controller motherboard. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-2B0B8AB8-E0D5-454C-A761-86ADFD3B9C65" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to request a license </title><note id="GUID-A621FDB0-88F3-4470-932A-616AB0ED67CC" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The SAM key should never be in the printer when you retrieve the dongle context file! 
</p></note><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-733DF7DD-F449-4FB2-A48B-47D68D23353E" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Verify the (service) SAM key is not in the printer. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Start the printer. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the Settings Editor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Access the settings editor via any web browser, by typing in the printer's: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> IP address, or 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Hostname 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Browse to: Support &gt; Licenses 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-8E30E611-D0C8-480B-9EDA-54F223F5FD0A" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> If no Product License number is available, skip steps 6 to 10 of the procedure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Otherwise the product License need to filled out in step 6 to 10. 
</p></note></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click the Product License ID of license value field: 
</p><fig id="GUID-7FB9808A-BA61-4EC9-BD3F-847422FCF541" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3FF85ABA-FF9C-4807-866D-AE8329157550-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3FF85ABA-FF9C-4807-866D-AE8329157550-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The System Administrator login window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-867EEA30-107D-4D06-8123-92330169F60A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-69ECDB8F-F007-4174-9819-671D101204EB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-69ECDB8F-F007-4174-9819-671D101204EB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Enter the System Administrator password and Log in. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The product license window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-8E94CCAF-2854-41DD-AFF6-4B4905660000" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1731C3DC-157F-43FF-AFE1-46A9C7651B85-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1731C3DC-157F-43FF-AFE1-46A9C7651B85-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Type in the product license for this printer and confirm the entry by clicking the OK button. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Create summary file of license dongle: 
</p><fig id="GUID-E8EDEE7A-5949-4EBD-BAAF-4A778B529D7B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-29DF0DA3-9BBF-4185-ADFE-2D6DBE3FAE02-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-29DF0DA3-9BBF-4185-ADFE-2D6DBE3FAE02-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> The System Administrator login window can pop-up. If so you need to login again. 
</p><fig id="GUID-BB6E9CE9-7DB0-4723-81FE-A544EE2E0484" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-69ECDB8F-F007-4174-9819-671D101204EB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-69ECDB8F-F007-4174-9819-671D101204EB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The Create and download summary file of license dongle window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-FEE13B9E-AF7D-4933-A0B6-543E81DFBB1E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-DF40F9B2-BF35-4C66-B1D7-62C060E764D6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DF40F9B2-BF35-4C66-B1D7-62C060E764D6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click Create summary file of license dongle. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> A &lt;dongle ID&gt;-SummaryFile.zip file is created: 
</p><fig id="GUID-DEC3C00E-9CB3-406D-B832-EE5596DC7E3B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8581157-D199-4519-AFE3-DDC055E772F0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8581157-D199-4519-AFE3-DDC055E772F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click the &lt;dongle ID&gt;-SummaryFile.zip file name to download the file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Store the file locally on your system. Example: 
</p><fig id="GUID-7ACD2699-58AB-40F2-9B45-A74593AFA87F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D7C0AE90-8FAC-45B1-857C-D4A3165F6B25-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D7C0AE90-8FAC-45B1-857C-D4A3165F6B25-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Request the new license by sending an e-mail to the back-office with the&lt;dongle ID&gt;-SummaryFile.zip file attached 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>